# WheelSense thesis (LaTeX)

- **Canonical faculty template (structure/style reference):** [`Thesis/Example/reporttemplate-0.0.1/`](Thesis/Example/reporttemplate-0.0.1/) (TU ECE `reporttemplate` v0.0.1). Prefer matching layout, front-matter patterns, and `TUthesis`/`mystyle` conventions to that tree unless a documented exception is required.
- **Submission PDF source:** build from [`Thesis/latex/thesis.tex`](Thesis/latex/thesis.tex) only.
- **Body chapters:** keep thesis body in [`Thesis/latex/content/chapters/`](Thesis/latex/content/chapters/) (`chapter1.tex` … `chapter5.tex`).
- **Do not reintroduce template chapter:** never add `\include{example}` or merge old sample chapter content into `thesis.tex`.
- **Cookbook separation:** [`Thesis/latex/doc/latex-writing-guide-chapter.tex`](Thesis/latex/doc/latex-writing-guide-chapter.tex) is reference/demo material, not thesis body.
- **Cookbook standalone build:** compile [`Thesis/latex/latex-writing-guide.tex`](Thesis/latex/latex-writing-guide.tex) separately from [`Thesis/latex/`](Thesis/latex/).
- **Metadata + bibliography:** project metadata in [`Thesis/latex/meta/info.tex`](Thesis/latex/meta/info.tex), references in [`Thesis/latex/bib/refs.bib`](Thesis/latex/bib/refs.bib).

## TU thesis formatting baseline

- **Paper size:** A4.
- **Margins:** top 1.5", left 1.5", right 1", bottom 1".
- **Default body font:** TH Sarabun New 16pt (or Times New Roman 12pt for English-thesis flow).
- **Line spacing:** 1.0 for TH Sarabun New content; 1.5 when using Times New Roman flow.
- **Paragraph indent:** 0.8".
- **Body alignment:** justified; avoid manual hard line breaks.
- **Numbers:** use Arabic numerals consistently.

## Page numbering policy

- Preliminary section pages (e.g. abstract, acknowledgements, table of contents) use Arabic numbers in parentheses, e.g. `(1)`.
- Main body pages use Arabic numbers without parentheses.
- Page numbers stay top-right with consistent offsets.
- Divider pages (e.g. part/appendix title pages) are not counted and do not show page numbers.

## Chapter and heading discipline

- Start each chapter on a new page.
- Keep heading hierarchy consistent: `\section` -> `\subsection` -> deeper levels only when needed.
- Do not hard-code figure/table/equation numbers in prose; use labels and `\ref`.
- Keep figure and table numbering chapter-scoped through LaTeX auto-numbering.

## Figures, tables, citations

- Keep figure/table captions formal and precise; explain what is shown, not result discussion text.
- Place chapter-specific figure files in chapter folders under `latex/assets/figures/`.
- For Chapter 1, keep files under `latex/assets/figures/chapter1/` to match existing `\IfFileExists` patterns.
- Use one citation style consistently across the thesis once chosen by program/faculty.
- Add all cited sources to [`latex/bib/refs.bib`](latex/bib/refs.bib); avoid manual fake numbering.

## Writing style (Thai thesis)

- Use formal academic Thai; keep technical English terms where they are clearer than Thai coinages (e.g. RSSI fingerprinting, KNN, MCP, BLE beacon).
- Keep claims evidence-based and avoid overclaiming beyond presented data.
- In `enumerate`, avoid extra vertical space between items while preserving normal paragraph spacing around lists.
- In Chapter 1, retain local list-spacing control via `\begingroup...\setlist[enumerate]{itemsep=0pt, parsep=0pt,...}\endgroup`.

## Compile and validation workflow

- Build from `latex/` using the project sequence (XeLaTeX + biber + XeLaTeX passes).
- After significant edits, verify:
  - no undefined references,
  - no missing citations,
  - no missing figure files,
  - chapter include order remains 1-5 in `thesis.tex`.
